        <a href={ctaSecondary} class="btn-secondary">Get a free demo</a>
      </div>
      <p class="mt-3 text-xs text-ink-500">14-day free trial · No card required · Cancel anytime</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="bg-white">
    <div class="container-narrow py-16 sm:py-20">
      <span class="eyebrow">What it does</span>
      <h2 class="h2 mt-3">What GST return filing software actually does</h2>
      <p class="mt-4 text-[17px] leading-relaxed text-ink-700">Most "filing" software does not file for you — it makes filing painless. As you raise GST invoices and record purchases, the software keeps <strong>return-ready books</strong> and produces <strong>GSTR-1</strong> (outward supplies) and <strong>GSTR-3B</strong> (summary) data you can upload to the GST portal, or file through a <strong>GST Suvidha Provider (GSP)</strong>. The best tools also reconcile your purchases against <strong>GSTR-2B</strong> so you don't lose input tax credit. Nidhi Books, Zoho Books and TallyPrime all generate return-ready exports; you or your CA do the final submission.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

